IBM, Walt Disney share losses contribute to Dow's 187-point fall

The Dow Jones Industrial Average is declining Monday afternoon with shares of IBM and Walt Disney facing the biggest declines for the price-weighted average. The Dow DJIA, +0.52% was most recently trading 187 points lower (-0.7%), as shares of IBM IBM, +2.11% and Walt Disney DIS, +2.59% are contributing to the blue-chip gauge's intraday decline. IBM's shares have declined $2.71 (2.0%) while those of Walt Disney are off $2.00, or 1.4%, combining for an approximately 32-point drag on the Dow. Procter & Gamble PG, -0.06%, Home Depot HD, -0.03%, and Pfizer PFE, -0.48% are also contributing significantly to the decline. A $1 move in any one of the 30 components of the Dow results in a 6.78-point swing.